05_chapter04_synopsis_01

Reisha confronted a suspicious dealer in a room of a brothel
in the reconstruction district and extracted information
from him.

What he was dealing turned out to be special ore mined from
the same pit Reisha had been confined in, along with workers
who were no longer of any use.
05_chapter04_synopsis_02

It was the dealer's job to secretly deliver these to an
experimental facility within the royal capital.
05_chapter04_synopsis_03

From his manner of speaking, it was inferred that the other
party in the deal was not just any villain, but someone who
wielded a certain degree of power within the royal capital.
05_chapter04_synopsis_04

Reisha threatened the dealer and made her way to the scene
of the transaction. The ones waiting for her, clad in
suspicious magical garments, were at the ruins of a fort now
unused, close to the central royal capital.
05_chapter04_synopsis_06

After fending off those men, she found traces of ore and
workers likely brought from the mining pit, just as the
dealer had testified, along with a teleportation magic
circle that probably led somewhere...
05_chapter04_synopsis_07

"Indeed, the current situation in the royal capital is
chaotic. However, security within the territory should still
be enforced. Why is such villainy overlooked in this place
so close to the royal capital...?"

"Why has the royal capital changed so much while I was away
searching for the sword...?"

Foreboding numerous calamities, she resolved to proceed
alone into the depths, anxiety weighing heavy on her heart.
